<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="msapplication-navbutton-color" content="#EFE">

    <meta name="mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes">
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes">
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-title" content="Example">
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-status-bar-style" content="black-translucent">

    <link rel="icon" type="image/jpg" sizes="32x32" href="dril.jpg">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/jpg" sizes="96x96" href="dril.jpg">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/jpg" sizes="16x16" href="dril.jpg">

    <title>Dril bits</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/index.css">


  </head>

  <body>
    <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8" id="twitter-wjs"></script>
    
    <ul id="navbar">
      <li> <a onclick="openAbout()">About</a> </li>
      <li> <a href="/Download">Download.txt</a> </li>
      <li class="right">
        <label class="switch">
          <input id="dark-mode" type="checkbox">
          <span class="slider"></span>
        </label>
      </li>
      <li class="right"> <span>Dark mode</span> </li>
    </ul>
    
    <h1>Dril bits</h1>

    <div id="tweet-container-previous" class="hide" data-tweetid="">

    </div>

    <div id="tweet-container-display" data-tweetid=<%=""+ tweet.id %> >
      <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"">
        <a href=<%= "http://twitter.com/dril/status/" + tweet.id%>> </a>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div id="tweet-container-next" class="hide" data-tweetid=<%=""+ tweet2.id %> >
      <blockquote class="twitter-tweet">
        <a href=<%= "http://twitter.com/dril/status/" + tweet2.id %>> </a>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
    
    <br>

    <ul id="buttons">
      <a title="R" id="random" class="control hide">Random</a>
      <br>
      <a title="Backspace" id="back" class="control disable">Back</a>
      <a title="Enter" id="next" class="control">Another one</a>
      
    </ul>

    <dialog class="about" id="about"> 
      <button onclick="about.close()" class="closeModal">Ã—</button>
      <p>Get a random <a href="https://twitter.com/dril?s=20">@dril</a> tweet</p>
      <p>Out of 10+ years and 10k+ posts, you can always find some hidden gems that may have slipped under the radar.</p>
      <p>It includes retweets and replys too, so not every tweet was written by @dril</p>
      <p>If you want all dril tweets in here as a neat JSON file with the text, the date and the id
          for each tweet, you can get them on the following link. It looks like this:</p>
      <p>{<br>&emsp;"text": "no",<br>&emsp;"id": "922321981",<br>&emsp;"date": "2008-09-15T13:25:20.000Z"<br>}</p>
      <a href="/DownloadJSON">Download JSON</a> <br>
      <a href="/DownloadDisplay">Download Display</a>
    </dialog>

    <script defer src="history.js"></script>
    <script defer src="index.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
